# Find the service which makes it possible to run specific tasks following a regular
# schedule
cron
# cron runs tasks called cron jobs that was scheduled in crontab in the background.
# (sudo) crontab -l -cmd lists the scheduled tasks.
# crontab -e | sudo crontab -u root -e to add your scheduled task. 
# For eg. you can run a backup of all your user accounts at 5 am every week then,
# 0 5 * * 1 tar -zcf /var/backups/home.tgz /home/
# minute hour dom month dow command
# dom - day of the month ; dow - day of the week